To this end the Central Bank shall:

1. issue licenses and define the licensing process;

2. prepare and keep up to date a list of licensed banks which shall be published in the Official Gazette

of the Kingdom of Cambodia and in the Bulletin of the National Bank of Cambodia;

3. be empowered to issue regulations for the implementation of this law which authorise the Central

Bank to determine, in particular the:
1. amount of minimum capital and the nature of the assets it is backed with;
2. prudential ratios regarding particularly liquidity, solvency, risk diversification, foreign exchange exposure,
and market risk exposure;
3. valuation rules for accounting balances;
4. conditions under which participations can be taken and held in the capital of a covered entity or a
financial institution;
5. conditions under which participations can be taken and held in the capital of other banking or financial
companies;
6. debts which must be regarded as doubtful, and the provisioning thereof;
7. the chart of accounts, the related accounting standards, the rules for the consolidation of accounts, and
the rules of the disclosure of accounting statements;
8. conditions applicable to the banking and financial operations that may be carried out in their relations
with customers;
9. organization of interbank joint services, including the centralization of financial information, risks, and
overdue debts;
10. granting of individual, exceptional, and temporary exemptions;
11. requirements and authorization rules concerning modifications in the business name, legal form, capital
distribution, management and activities of a covered entity, or of the head office in the case of a branch
of a foreign bank;
12. practice of door to door selling of banking or financial services;
13. after consultation with the covered entities’ professional association, the rules governing the operation
of a deposit guarantee system;
14. and, generally speaking, the modalities for enforcing this law in light of the differences concerning the
legal form of covered entities, the scope of their network, and the nature of their activities.

4. it publishes all regulations issued by virtue of its authority in the Official Gazette of the Kingdom of

Cambodia and in the Bulletin of National Bank of Cambodia;

5. it supervises the banking system through permanent off-site monitoring and periodic on-site

examinations of each covered entity; if the need arises, on-site examinations may be extended to a

subsidiary of a covered entity or to any other related entities, including shareholders;

6. it organises or supervises any interbank settlement system;

7. it may require that covered entities, public offices, auditors, and any other individual or legal entity

disclose information considered as useful for its mission;

8. and it may, in accordance with the conditions defined in Articles 52 to 54 of this law, take

disciplinary action.

